Description: Green glazed composition shabti of Tjainehebu with a lappet-wig, a modelled face with a beard and crossed hands in relief holding an adze, a hoe and the string of the seed-bag that hangs over the shoulder; the leg section is inscribed with ten rows of Hieroglyphs; back pillar and a plinth.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: R J Moss & Co
